oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Masonic Building Collapse, View down S. Third Street, 1949
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of an elevated view of the southwest wall of the Masonic Building after the initial collapse. The interior of the building is visible through a large hole in the side of the building. The view is partially obscured by the Dunlop's Garage building. A crowd of people is visible, standing in the road across Commerce Street.
